CboSchedule="This box allows the user to select 1 of 6 schedules for line tracking."
SelectedSchedule="Selected Schedule."
ScheduleGroupNo="The motion group for the selected schedule."
FrameTaught="The frame for this schedule is defined."
PartDetectDist="This item indicates the distance from the center line of the robot at its zero position to the part detect switch.  This allows paint programs that were taught in one booth to play back correctly in a different booth. This value is for viewing only."
EncoderTeachDistance="This item indicates the distance from the center line of the robot at its zero position to the part detect switch.  This allows paint programs that were taught in one booth to play back correctly in a different booth. This value is for viewing only."
EncoderThreshold="This item represents the actual speed the conveyor will have to reach before the encoder hardware will inform the robot that the conveyor is moving.  A typical pulse threshold value is 5 mm/sec. This value is for viewing only."
EncoderMinDistance="This item indicates the minimum distance, in millimeters, that the conveyor must travel before the system will acknowledge a new part detect signal.  This prevents the controller from receiving more than one part detect signal for the same part.  A typical minimum detect distance is 1000 mm. This value is for viewing only."
EncoderMaxDistance="This item indicates a measured distance from the part detect switch.  When a part has traveled past this point on the conveyor, the part has traveled too far for the job to be painted.  Therefore, a part that has past this point before the job is started will be skipped and an error message will be displayed. If this value is set to 0, parts will never be skipped.  PaintTool will attempt to paint all parts.  Otherwise, the value of maximum travel to start is used to determine the distance a part can travel before it is skipped. This value is for viewing only."
EncoderAverage="This item is a value that will help to smooth robot motion when tracking the conveyor.  If you have a conveyor that does not move smoothly, the average should be a larger value to smooth the motion.  A typical encoder average value is 25. This value is for viewing only."
EncoderScaleFactor="This item is the physical relationship between the robot and the conveyor, measured in encoder pulses per millimeter of conveyor travel.  For every millimeter the conveyor moves, the encoder will return a certain number of counts (pulses).  The scale value will vary per site. This value is for viewing only."
HoldCounts="This number represents a distance in CM from the part detect when the conveyor will be held if the robot has not completed color change.  Robots 4,5,6 add 701 CM to the hold count to get the total distance from the part detect."
LastTrigger="This is the last Part Detect the robot saw. The value shown is in encoder counts.  This valve is for viewing only."
BodyDistance="This is the distance the current part has traveled in mm after passing the Part Detect switch.  This value is for viewing only."
InBounds1="During production, the system will wait until the part travels past the inbounds window before the robot will start processing the part. The process can call for one of 10 defined Inbounds/Outbounds groups."
OutBounds1="If the part travels past the outbounds window, the part cannot be processed and an error will be displayed . The process can call for one of 10 defined Inbounds/Outbounds groups."
