CboAirType="This box allows the user to select the Air Type to configure."

AAModeSelect="This setting determines the source of AccuAir Open/Closed Loop mode selection. Source selections include Cell Input, Pendant, Network, and Other."
AAPctToleranceBand="Percent tolerance band is a +/- percentage deviation allowable from the setpoint to enable the setpoint reached output. This value is applied to all flow rates where the percent tolerance band value is greater than the minimum tolerance band." 
AAMinToleranceBand="Minimum tolerance band is the fixed +/- deviation allowable from the setpoint to enable the setpoint reached output. This value is applied to all flow rates where the minimum tolerance value is greater than the percentage tolerance."
AASampleAmount="Sample amount filters the incoming pulse train from the flow meter. Sample amount uses an averaging algorithm for preferential weighting of the old flow rate when calculating the new flow rate. The algorithm is as follows: Average Rate New = ([{sample amount-1} * Average Rate Old] + Instantaneous Rate New) / Sample Amount."
AANormalGainMod="This number defines what amount of flow rate error AccuFlow will attempt to correct for in a single step when the color parameter Pulsing pump supply is set to no. Setting this number too high might cause instability while setting it too low will cause slow response to flow errors."

AASensorMaxRange="The maximum flow rate that the sensor is capable of measuring."
AAScalingMaxRdgSLPM="The actual flow rate when sensor output is at or near maximum (Scaling Max Reading(mA))."
AAScalingMaxRdgMA="The maximum sensor output (mA) when flow rate is at or near the maximum that it is capable of measuring."
AASensorZeroRdgMA="The minimum sensor output (mA) when flow rate is at zero."
AAEquipLearnDone="This item controls the calibration method that automatically determines the characteristics of air equipment on the robot. It can have one of four values; Redo, Not Done, Done, or Disabled. When set to Redo, the equipment is re-learned during the next calibration and automatically set to Done if the calibration is successful."
AATriggerDelay="The length of time expected from the electrical trigger on signal to the detection of flow that is within 10% of target. This parameter compensates for pneumatic trigger signal lag. It is determined automatically."
AAFlowDelay="This item is the fixed delay for any flow change that occurs without a trigger transition. It compensates for I/P transducer reaction time and other delays that are independent of flow rate. It is determined automatically."
AATimeUp="The rate at which the system ramped up to the maximum flow rate requested when a calibration was performed. The engineering unit displayed is in milliseconds/1000 counts."
AATimeDown="The rate at which the system ramped down to the minimum flow rate requested when a calibration was performed. The engineering unit displayed is in milliseconds/1000 counts." 

AAHystCheckEnable="If set to YES, AccuAir wil automatically determinr the Hysteresis value at the end of every calibration sequence."
AARemoteTare="This item indicates whether a tare (zeroing) check will occur each time production mode is entered or a calibration is completed. During a tare check, the Leak Detect While Zeroing condition is checked and a signal is sent to the flow meter(s) that causes them to tare (zero)."
AALevelingTries="This value is used during calibration to specify the number of flow rate samples that must be within tolerance of the setpoint before the flow rate is considered to be a true reading."
AACalTimeOut="The length of time that AccuAir allows for each calibration section to complete before aborting the calibration sequence. Sections are; Determining Gain, Determining Max Flow Rate, Flow Step Down, Hysteresis Tests, Time up and Time Down."
AACalStepDelay="This time value is used during the calibration cycle as a software-selectable delay, assuring system stabilization prior to reading the flow rate."
AATablePoint2="The value in engineering units that will be used as the target flow rate for point #2 of the calibration table. This point defines the lowest setpoint which wil be used for updating the calibration table. closed loop corrections will still be made below this value."

AAFlowInTolTries="The number of flow rate samples that must be consecutively within tolerance before a decision is made to update the dynamic calibration table. (ref. Percent Tolerance Band, Minimum Tolerance Band settings)"
AAIndPointShiftBand="Independent Point Shift Band (IPSB) is used during the adaptive point update routine within AccuAir. IPSB has comparison functions like the adaptive tolerance band, but instead of setting a status flag, IPSB reslopes the flow vs. command data. The benefit of IPSB is quicker response and update time when flow rate is incorrect due to changes in supply pressure. The IPSB is expressed as a percentage of change between the existing points on the dynamic table (for example, 300 = 30%)."

AAAdaptiveTolerance="This item is used in the determination of how far the Dynamic Calibration table has rotated away from the Reference Calibration table during operation as the alarm level. When the percentage difference exceeds this tolerance, the Adapted Out of Tolerance alarm is posted to alert the operator of dramatic change from the original calibration."
AAMaxError="The allowable flow rate error (setpoin - actual flow rate) averaged over an entire job at one second intervals. If the flow rate error is greater than this setting, the Flow Rate Average Error Excessive error will be posted."
AAMaxControlOut="This setting is the longest time that AccuAir will allow the control output to be at either extreme (min or max) and still not reach the flow rate setpoint before entering open loop mode for the reminder of the job. An alarm will be posted to alert the operator to this condition. A value of zero disables this alarm."
AAMinSetpointReached="This setting is the maximum amount of time allowed for AccuAir to regain the flow setpoint. If the setpoint cannot be reached within this time, the Failed To Reach Setpoint Alarm will be posted. A value of zero will disable this alarm."
AAZeroFlowTimeout="When the flowrate setpoint is zero, the air flow measurement must remain at zero for this amount of time. Otherwise, the Zero Air Flow Timeout alarm is posted and control is temporarily fored to open loop mode. A value of zero disables this alarm."
AAGracePeriod="A fixed period of applicator on time at the beginning of a job during which flow rate errors will not be posted. This applies specifically to alarms due to Max Control Out and Min Setpoint Reached."
AASlowLeakFlow="This item is the air flow rate at which the Slow Air Leak Detected alarm will be generated. This value must be less than half of the value of the Fast Leak Rate and greater than a low flow which is considered zero. A value of zero disables this alarm. Note: This function is only applicable to guns that trigger the air off."
AAFastLeakFlow="This item is the air flow rate at which the Fast Air Leak Detected alarm will be generated. This value must be at least twice the value of the Slow Leak Rate. A value of zero disables this alarm. Note: This function is only applicable to guns that trigger the air off."
AALeakWhenZero="This item is the air flow rate at which the Leak Detect When Zeroing alarm will be generated."

AAAdaptEnable1="When set to YES, closed loop control of Atomizing air (guns) or Shaping Air (bells) is enabled."
AAAdaptEnable2="When set to YES, closed loop control of Fan air (guns) is enabled. Channel 2 is not used in bell systems."

